HEADWORD: Eye-saint
<hw>Eye"-saint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An object of
interest to the eye; one worshiped with the eyes.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That's the <qex>eye-saint</qex>, I know,⟦br⟧
Among young gallants.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eyesalve</ent>⟦br⟧
